<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1151,1285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="525">
This monobasic genus is the only known member of tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" box="[798,893,1151,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dryptini">Dryptini</taxonomicName>
from the Neotropical region. The single species, known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[353,421,1187,1213]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="525">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(“Ega”, today Tefé, in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[810,933,1187,1213]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="3" pageNumber="525">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
), is easily distinguishable by its unique combination of characters, i.e. elytra with strong, smooth costae, intervals wide and transversely striate; apex of elytra with external angle spiniform; claws smooth.
</paragraph>
